## 12. Required API Endpoints

### Public

```txt
GET /api/categories
GET /api/gallery
GET /api/gallery/featured
GET /api/settings
```

### Admin Auth

```txt
POST /api/admin/login
POST /api/admin/logout optional
GET /api/admin/me optional
```

### Admin Categories

```txt
GET /api/admin/categories
POST /api/admin/categories
PATCH /api/admin/categories/:id
DELETE /api/admin/categories/:id
```

### Admin Gallery

```txt
GET /api/admin/gallery
POST /api/admin/gallery
PATCH /api/admin/gallery/:id
DELETE /api/admin/gallery/:id
```

### Admin Upload

```txt
POST /api/admin/upload
```

This endpoint should accept `multipart/form-data`.

Expected response:

```json
{
  "data": {
    "url": "https://res.cloudinary.com/...",
    "publicId": "...",
    "width": 1000,
    "height": 1000,
    "format": "jpg",
    "bytes": 123456
  }
}
```

### Admin Settings

```txt
GET /api/admin/settings
PATCH /api/admin/settings
```

---

## 13. API Response Format

Use consistent response shapes.

Success object:

```json
{
  "data": {}
}
```

Success list:

```json
{
  "items": []
}
```

Error:

```json
{
  "error": {
    "message": "Human readable message",
    "code": "ERROR_CODE"
  }
}
```

---

## 14. Frontend Integration Notes

The frontend should call the backend using a configurable API base URL.

Recommended helper:

```ts
const API_BASE_URL = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL ?? "";
```

Then API requests can use:

```ts
fetch(`${API_BASE_URL}/api/gallery`)
```

If using Vercel rewrites, `API_BASE_URL` can be empty and requests can use `/api/...`.

Files likely to change:

- `src/lib/api/client.ts`
- `src/lib/admin/api.ts`
- `src/routes/index.tsx`
- `src/routes/admin/login.tsx`
- `src/routes/admin/index.tsx`

The public gallery should eventually fetch from:

```txt
GET /api/categories
GET /api/gallery
GET /api/gallery/featured
GET /api/settings
```

The admin dashboard should use:

```txt
POST /api/admin/login
POST /api/admin/upload
POST /api/admin/gallery
PATCH /api/admin/gallery/:id
DELETE /api/admin/gallery/:id
POST /api/admin/categories
PATCH /api/admin/categories/:id
DELETE /api/admin/categories/:id
PATCH /api/admin/settings
```

